  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: \n\n```\nGeth\nVersion: 1.4.18-stable-c72f5459\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.6\nOS: linux\nGOPATH=/home/konrad/.gopath\nGOROOT=/usr/local/go\n```\n\nOS & Version: Linux\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nI have a datadir at `~/.ethereumdatadirs/mordengeth` with a partially synced testnet chain in `~/.ethereumdatadirs/mordengeth/testnet`.\nIn order to resync testnet from scratch, I run the command\n\n```\n$ geth --testnet --datadir ~/.ethereumdatadirs/mordengeth removedb\nRemove local database? [y/N] y\ny\nRemoving chaindata...\nRemoved in 73.631Âµs\n```\n\nNow starting the client with\n\n```\n$ geth --testnet --datadir .ethereumdatadirs/mordengeth\n```\n\nshould sync from scratch.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nThe testnet data was still there, i.e. not syncing from scratch.\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\n1) Start syncing the testnet in a certain datadir\n2) Stop and call `removedb` as described above\n3) Check for testnet data in datadir\n#### Backtrace\n\nnot applicable\n",
